$ Coloring graphics in R: gray shades

With → development/languages/R/functions/gray[`gray`] it's possible to create a → development/languages/R/graphics/coloring/palettes of gray shades and then to apply the colors to the graphic.

In the following example, the »darkness« of a color corresponds to the rank of height of the bar:
gh|about-r|/graphics/coloring/gray-shades.R||

→ development/languages/R/graphics/coloring/gray-shades.png

sa:
  → development/languages/R/graphics/coloring

  → development/languages/R/functions/barplot[`barplot`],
  → development/languages/R/functions/rank[`rank`],
  → development/languages/R/functions/length[`length`]
